               <head>Treatises on medicine</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068424">
                  <summary>Two treatises on medicine. Other contents: 1v-2v, Fī l-nabż: tract in Arabic on diagnosis from the pulse; 2v, Bāb dar tang kardan-i farj-i zanān: brief extract from a treatise in Persian on narrowing the vulva; 104v-100r (written in reverse order to rest of codex), various notes and lists, including: 103r-102v, poem on diet, headed Tadbīr-i ma’kūl; 102r-101v, Mus-hilāt-i ṣafrā; 101r-100v, Mus-hilāt-i balgham va sawdā. Purchased from A al-Shakri, 20 January 2006. </summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083158" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16272-item1">
                     <locus from="2v" to="75v">ff. 2v-75v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>A general treatise on medicine, part of which is an abridgement of the same author’s better-known <title>Z̲akhīrah-'i Khvārazmshāhī</title>. By Ismā‘īl ibn al-Ḥusayn al-Ḥasanī al-Jurjānī (d. 535/1136 or 531/1132). See FNKhF I, pp. 473-4; Storey, PL II/2 E pp. 209-10. Other BL copies: I.O. Islamic 1778, I.O. Islamic 2228 (damaged and defective), see Ethé IOL I cols. 1249-52.
                        </p>
                        <p>Text may well have been copied at roughly the same time as the second treatise in this volume. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_731">al-Aghrāz̤ al-ṭibbīyah va al-mabāḥis̲ al-ʿalāʾīyah</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_47935028">Ismāʿīl ibn al-Ḥusayn al-Ḥasanī al-Jurjānī, 1042 or 1043-1136 or 1137</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_47935028">اسماعيل بن حسن جرجانى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083158" n="2" xml:id="Uk_Or_16272-item2">
                     <locus from="76r" to="98v">ff. 76r-98v</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22130">Ḥaqāʾiq asrār al-aṭibbāʾ</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A treatise in Arabic on medicine, composed by <persName key="person_f7262" role="aut">Masʿūd ibn Muḥammad al-Sanjarī (?) al-Ṭabīb</persName>, for <persName key="person_f7479" role="pat">Qāsim ibn ʿAvvāq ibn Jaʿfar</persName>, described as <persName key="person_f7479" role="pat">al-ʿAlīm al-ʿĀdil Ṣadr al-Dawlah va al-Dīn Malik al-Vuzarāʾ</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work comprises three parts (fann), which are subdivided into sections (qism).
1: Muhayyāt al-ashyā’ allatī yata‘allaq (sic) bi-kulliyyāt al-ṭibb va rusūmihā l-taqarrubiyya: general principles of medicine.
2: Kayfiyyat al-a‘māl va l-ṣinā‘at al-muṭa‘allaqa bi-uṣūl al-ṭibb: necessary skills and operations.
3: Kamiyyat aqsām al-umūr al-munqasima inqisāman kulliyyan: the number of detailed aspects.
</p>
                        <p>Colophon dated 2 Ramaz̤ān 1178/23 February 1765 </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7262">Masʿūd ibn Muḥammad al-Sanjarī (?) al-Ṭabīb</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
